data.text:
For the group with a similar name, see Mini Patrol.

For the book, see The Junior Patrollers.

The Junior Patrollers are a group of Pomeranians that is formed by Nano, Mini, and Tot in PAW Patrol: The Mighty Movie. The three enroll in the PAW Patrol's Junior Patroller program and are mentored by Liberty as they have no experience when it comes to rescuing. The team made their debut in the PAW Patrol series through Season 10's "Mighty Pups vs. The Mayor of the Universe" and made several other appearances in the new Mighty Pups sub-series alongside Liberty.

When equipped with a meteorite crystal, the trio all have the same superpower of multiplication, in which they can make numerous duplicates of themselves.

Members

Nano

Mini

Tot

Nicknames

"Liberty and the Poms" (by the synopsis of Season 10's "Mighty Pups vs. The Mayor of the Universe")

"Three puffballs" (by Liberty in some of the books, aimed to Nano, Mini, and Tot)

"The Poms" (shown in some of the merchandises, aimed to Nano, Mini, and Tot)

"Puffballs" (by Liberty in PAW Patrol: The Mighty Movie, aimed to Nano, Mini, and Tot)
